This paper deals with the problem of describing visual contents of a video sequence with natural language, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves a novel encoder-decoder-reconstructor architecture, which is a deep learning model and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
